Family Migration
search links (csearch) (census year)
hik, year, serial, loc

Places
location, stateicp, region, zone

Household (census year)
year, serial, loc, farm, urban, sizepl, hhtype, gq, gqtype, gqtyped

Family (census year)
year, serial, loc, histid, birthyr, sex, histid_hh, pernum, relate, related, histid_sp, histid_pop, histid_mom,
	steppop, stepmom, age, hik, race, bpl, bpld, sursim, slvhcat
	
Work Status
year, serial, loc, histid, school, labforce, occ1950

Slaveholder (processed from individual slv fields - adult or child in slaveholding household 1850/1860)
year, serial, histid, slvhcat

1. create loc codes (coalesce, stateicp, countyicp, region)
2. create search links union of hik, year, serial, loc from cr(yyyy)
3. create basehiks (year, loc, category)
4. search csearch (all) for instances of basehiks in census households (append new hiks) recursive (up/down/up/down)
5. create studylinks (hik-year-serial-loc) for all recursed hiks

6. extract family census records from cr(yyyy) via studylinks (linked and unlinked per year/serial)
7. extract household census records from cr(yyyy) via studylinks




